full_description:

Enterprise AI adoption looks straightforward in slide decks and painful in practice. In this talk, Alexander C. S. Hendorf distils five of the most consequential things every leader should know before scaling AI inside a large organisation — drawn from years of advisory work with companies moving AI from experiment to production.
This is not a hype reel. It's a candid look at the strategic, organisational, and technical realities that determine whether AI initiatives create lasting value or become expensive distractions.
What you'll take away:

The five questions every executive should answer before scaling AI
Why most enterprise AI projects stall — and what unblocks them
Where to invest, where to wait, and where to walk away
How to align leadership, engineering, and data teams around outcomes that matter

---

About the speaker

Alexander C. S. Hendorf is an independent AI & Open Source strategy advisor, working with leadership teams and engineering organizations from boardroom to code. He helps companies move AI from experimentation into reliable, sovereign systems — drawing on a deep network across the Open Source AI ecosystem and decades of hands-on experience with Python, data, and ML infrastructure.

A long-standing program chair and keynote speaker at international Python and data conferences (PyData, EuroPython, PyConDE), Alexander is a recurring voice on Open Source, Digital Sovereignty, and applied AI strategy.

🌐 Website: https://hendorf.com
🔗 LinkedIn: https://www.linkedin.com/in/hendorf/

For AI strategy, Open Source AI, and high-stakes AI advisory engagements: https://hendorf.com

